This paper deals with Bandwidth Allocation Models (BAMs) in networks, specifically in IP/MPLS/DS-TE networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses resource allocation and policy behavior, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions security concerns, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of network resource utilization, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
